headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 27 points, Seth Curry added 22 and the Brooklyn Nets broke free midway through the fourth quarter Saturday for a 110-95 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets pull away late, take down Clippers 110-95

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis had 31 points and 10 rebounds, Kyle Kuzma added 23 points, eight rebounds and six assists, and the Washington Wizards beat the Utah Jazz 121-112 on Saturday night for their season-high third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis has 31, Wizards beat Jazz 121-112 for 3rd straight

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 28 of his season-high 43 points in the first half as the Boston Celtics beat the Detroit Pistons 117-108 on Saturday night for their sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 43, Celtics beat Pistons for 6th straight win

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored 22 points, Myles Turner had 19 points and 10 rebounds, and the Indiana Pacers used a dominant fourth quarter to beat the Toronto Raptors 118-104 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers use big fourth quarter to beat Raptors 118-104

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had a season-high 42 points and 10 rebounds as the Philadelphia 76ers turned a blistering shooting performance in the first half into a 121-109 win over the Atlanta Hawks on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores season-best 42 points, 76ers top Hawks 121-109

headlines.description: — Max Strus and the Miami Heat finally enjoyed a rare easy win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Strus scores 31, Heat roll past sliding Hornets 132-115

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 42 points, 13 rebounds and 10 assists for his third triple-double of the season, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Portland Trail Blazers 117-112 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic's triple-double, Dinwiddie's late run lead Mavs' win

events.name: Houston Rockets at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 26 points and Brandon Ingram iced the game with six points in a 13-0 run in the final 2:07 to power the New Orleans Pelicans to a 119-106 victory over the Houston Rockets on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Zion Williamson scores 26 as Pelicans beat Rockets 119-106
